snippet: The Obama administration said Sunday that 100,000 people had submitted applications for health insurance on the first day of open enrollment, although some returning customers had trouble remembering their usernames and passwords.
abstract: Health officials report that 100,000 people submitted health insurance applications online on first day of open enrollment, noting that none of the technical issues that shadowed last year's enrollment are impeding process in 2014.
lead_paragraph: The Obama administration said Sunday that 100,000 people had submitted applications for health insurance on the first day of open enrollment, although some returning customers had trouble remembering their usernames and passwords.
